<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="56" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,320,2039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,680,706]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Description.</emphasis>
Habitus typical of the genus. Body length 
<quantity box="[854,996,681,707]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="0.9" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.7">0.7–1.1 mm</quantity>
. Color light greyish-blue. Tegumental granulation coarse and uniform, 5–6 granules between setae p 
<subScript attach="left" box="[844,852,735,749]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">1</subScript>
on Abd. V (
<figureCitation box="[986,1070,716,743]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,190,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1646]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–16. H. cretensis sp. nov.: 12, tegumental granulation and chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 13, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 14, postantennal organ and ocelli; 15, claw III with empodial appendage; 16, dens and mucro. Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669060/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,320,2039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
Body setae short (slightly longer on last abdominal segments), fine and smooth. Body sensilla (s) about two times longer than microsetae, fine and smooth. Chaetotaxy of head typical of the genus, with complete set of v-setae (
<bibRefCitation author="Ellis, W. N." box="[159,278,824,850]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" pagination="221 - 326" refId="ref4479" refString="Ellis, W. N. (1976) Autumn fauna of Collembola from Central Crete. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 119, 221 - 326." type="journal article" year="1976">Ellis 1976</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[289,375,824,851]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Fig. 9 e</figureCitation>
). Dorsal chaetotaxy of Th. I–III and Abd. IV–VI as in 
<bibRefCitation author="Ellis, W. N." box="[980,1107,824,850]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" pagination="221 - 326" refId="ref4479" refString="Ellis, W. N. (1976) Autumn fauna of Collembola from Central Crete. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 119, 221 - 326." type="journal article" year="1976">Ellis (1976</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[1117,1202,824,851]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Figs 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1213,1288,824,851]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,190,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1646]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–16. H. cretensis sp. nov.: 12, tegumental granulation and chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 13, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 14, postantennal organ and ocelli; 15, claw III with empodial appendage; 16, dens and mucro. Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669060/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">12b–d</figureCitation>
). Th. I with 3 + 3 setae. Th. II with setae m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[475,483,879,893]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">2</subScript>
, m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[518,526,879,893]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">3</subScript>
and m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[602,610,879,893]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">4</subScript>
present. Th. III with setae m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[929,937,879,893]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">2</subScript>
and m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1013,1021,879,893]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">3</subScript>
absent and setae m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1237,1245,879,893]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">4</subScript>
present. Abd. IV with setae p 
<subScript attach="left" box="[284,292,915,929]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">3</subScript>
and p 
<subScript attach="left" box="[361,369,915,929]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">7</subScript>
present. Abd. V with setae p 
<subScript attach="left" box="[687,695,915,929]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">2</subScript>
present and setae m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[921,929,915,929]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">1</subScript>
and m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1005,1013,915,929]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">3</subScript>
usually present (
<figureCitation box="[1201,1284,896,923]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,190,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1646]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–16. H. cretensis sp. nov.: 12, tegumental granulation and chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 13, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 14, postantennal organ and ocelli; 15, claw III with empodial appendage; 16, dens and mucro. Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669060/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Subcoxae I, II, III with 1, 2, 3 setae, respectively. Microsensillum on Th. II present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,320,2039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
Ant. IV with simple apical vesicle, subapical organite, microsensillum, 6–8 weakly differentiated cylindrical, curved sensilla (3 lateral and 3–5 dorsal) (
<figureCitation box="[627,708,1004,1031]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,190,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1646]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–16. H. cretensis sp. nov.: 12, tegumental granulation and chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 13, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 14, postantennal organ and ocelli; 15, claw III with empodial appendage; 16, dens and mucro. Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669060/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) and 5–7 short pointed setae in ventral field. Ant. III-organ with two long (outer) and two short (inner) sensilla. Microsensillum on Ant. III present. Ant. I with 7 setae (seta p’ absent).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,320,2039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
Ocelli: 8 + 8. Postantennal organ 1.7–2.0 as long as neighboring ocelli, with four lobes, the anterior pair slightly larger than posterior one. Accessory boss present, but sometimes hard to observe (
<figureCitation box="[1108,1192,1148,1175]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,190,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1646]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–16. H. cretensis sp. nov.: 12, tegumental granulation and chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 13, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 14, postantennal organ and ocelli; 15, claw III with empodial appendage; 16, dens and mucro. Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669060/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ellis, W. N." box="[1253,1374,1148,1174]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" pagination="221 - 326" refId="ref4479" refString="Ellis, W. N. (1976) Autumn fauna of Collembola from Central Crete. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 119, 221 - 326." type="journal article" year="1976">Ellis 1976</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Figs 9h–k</figureCitation>
). Labrum without apical papillae. Labral setae 5, 5, 4, prelabrals 4. Maxillary head as in 
<bibRefCitation author="Fjellberg, A." box="[1196,1382,1184,1211]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" refId="ref4537" refString="Fjellberg, A. (1998) The Collembola of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Part 1 Poduromorpha. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica. Brill, Leiden, Boston and Koln, 184 pp." type="book" year="1998">Fjellberg (1998)</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Fig. 11d</figureCitation>
. Lamella 1 broadened at tip, protruding beyond teeth, with two fringes of long cilia. Labial palp as shown in 
<bibRefCitation author="Fjellberg, A." box="[151,328,1256,1283]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" pagination="309 - 330" refId="ref4570" refString="Fjellberg, A. (1999) The labial palp in Collembola. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 237, 309 - 330." type="journal article" year="1999">Fjellberg (1999</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[339,406,1256,1283]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Outer maxillary lobe with two sublobal hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,320,2039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
Tibiotarsi I, II, III with 19, 19, 18 setae, respectively. Apical seta A1 weakly clavate, slightly longer than inner edge of claw. Claws with small inner tooth. Empodial appendage with narrow basal lamella. Ratio empodial appendage/inner edge of claws = 0.5–0.6 (
<figureCitation box="[600,680,1364,1391]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,190,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1646]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–16. H. cretensis sp. nov.: 12, tegumental granulation and chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 13, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 14, postantennal organ and ocelli; 15, claw III with empodial appendage; 16, dens and mucro. Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669060/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ellis, W. N." box="[735,853,1364,1390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" pagination="221 - 326" refId="ref4479" refString="Ellis, W. N. (1976) Autumn fauna of Collembola from Central Crete. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 119, 221 - 326." type="journal article" year="1976">Ellis 1976</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[864,945,1364,1391]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Fig. 9c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,320,2039]" box="[199,1002,1400,1427]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Ventral tube with four setae on each side. Retinaculum with 3 + 3 teeth.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,320,2039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
Furca well developed (ratio dens + mucro/inner edge of claw III = 2.7–3.0). Dorsal side of dens with 7 setae and with coarse, uniform granulation. Mucro slightly curved, with globular tip and rather high outer lamella ending just before the apex. Ratio dens/mucro = 2.5–3.2 (
<figureCitation box="[665,746,1508,1534]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,190,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1646]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–16. H. cretensis sp. nov.: 12, tegumental granulation and chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 13, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 14, postantennal organ and ocelli; 15, claw III with empodial appendage; 16, dens and mucro. Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669060/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ellis, W. N." box="[800,918,1508,1534]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" pagination="221 - 326" refId="ref4479" refString="Ellis, W. N. (1976) Autumn fauna of Collembola from Central Crete. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 119, 221 - 326." type="journal article" year="1976">Ellis 1976</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[929,1067,1508,1535]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Figs 9d, f, g</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,320,2039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
Anal spines short (ratio anal spines/inner edge of claws III = 0.3–0.5), slightly curved, on separate papillae of same length as spines (
<bibRefCitation author="Ellis, W. N." box="[408,528,1580,1606]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" pagination="221 - 326" refId="ref4479" refString="Ellis, W. N. (1976) Autumn fauna of Collembola from Central Crete. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 119, 221 - 326." type="journal article" year="1976">Ellis 1976</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[539,665,1580,1607]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1670,1694]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,190,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1646]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–16. H. cretensis sp. nov.: 12, tegumental granulation and chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 13, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 14, postantennal organ and ocelli; 15, claw III with empodial appendage; 16, dens and mucro. Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669060" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669060/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Figs 12a, b</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,748,1616,1643]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,320,2039]" box="[199,748,1616,1643]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1617,1643]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after the 
<typeStatus box="[528,576,1617,1643]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">type</typeStatus>
locality, 
<collectingRegion box="[679,743,1617,1643]" country="Greece" name="Kriti" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Crete</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="56" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,320,2039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1653,1679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ellis, W. N." box="[323,457,1652,1679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" pagination="221 - 326" refId="ref4479" refString="Ellis, W. N. (1976) Autumn fauna of Collembola from Central Crete. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 119, 221 - 326." type="journal article" year="1976">Ellis (1976)</bibRefCitation>
reported the occurrence of a form similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ellis" authorityYear="1976" box="[967,1065,1653,1678]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gisini">
<emphasis box="[967,1065,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">H. gisini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[1102,1166,1653,1679]" country="Greece" name="Kriti" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Crete</collectingRegion>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ellis" authorityYear="1976" box="[1178,1311,1652,1678]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gisini">
<emphasis box="[1178,1206,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">H.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[1249,1311,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">gisini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found at eleven sites, mainly inland around Iraklion and Rethymno, in anthropogenic habitats (e.g. roads, orchards, meadows) with clay, less often sandy, soil up to 
<quantity box="[627,697,1725,1751]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" unit="m" value="700.0">700 m</quantity>
a. s. l. This form differed from 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ellis" authorityYear="1976" box="[1048,1144,1725,1750]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gisini">
<emphasis box="[1048,1144,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">H. gisini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
not only in habitat preferences (the latter occurs in coastal habitats), but also in morphology (the author indicated the length of the empodium as a distinguishing feature). Ellis did not decide to describe 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ellis" authorityYear="1976" box="[829,963,1796,1822]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gisini">
<emphasis box="[829,857,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">H.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[901,963,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">gisini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new species because he did not have the opportunity to study the 
<typeStatus box="[469,517,1833,1859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ellis" authorityYear="1976" box="[654,750,1833,1858]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gisini">
<emphasis box="[654,750,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">H. gisini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. After redescription of this species and examination of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Ellis" authorityYear="1976" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gisini">
<emphasis box="[1373,1401,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">H.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[151,213,1869,1894]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">gisini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens from the collections of Ellis (NBCN) and DIBEC it became clear that they are morphologically distinct. As a consequence, this last form has been recognized as a species new to science – 
<taxonomicName authority="Skarżyński &amp; Gwiazdowicz, 2022" authorityName="Skarżyński &amp; Gwiazdowicz" authorityYear="2022" box="[1161,1293,1905,1930]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cretensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1161,1293,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">H. cretensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1299,1387,1905,1931]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1299,1387,1905,1931]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
The differences between them, as well as other species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tullberg" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[779,947,1940,1966]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manubrialis">
<emphasis box="[779,947,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">H. manubrialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Babenko, A. B. &amp; Chernova, N. M. &amp; Potapov, M. B. &amp; Stebaeva, S. K." box="[1091,1330,1940,1967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" refId="ref4360" refString="Babenko, A. B., Chernova, N. M., Potapov, M. B. &amp; Stebaeva, S. K. (1994) Collembola of Russia and adjacent countries. Family Hypogastruridae. Nauka, Moscow, 336 pp." type="book" year="1994">Babenko et al. (1994)</bibRefCitation>
that have a retinaculum with 3 + 3 teeth and a maxillary head of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Carl" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[797,920,1976,2002]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernalis">
<emphasis box="[797,920,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">H. vernalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[927,975,1977,2003]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">type</typeStatus>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fjellberg, A." box="[989,1157,1976,2003]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" pagination="89 - 99" refId="ref4506" refString="Fjellberg, A. (1984) Maxillary structures in Hypogastruridae (Collembola). Annales de la Societe Royale Zoologique de Bel- gique, 114, 89 - 99." type="journal article" year="1984">Fjellberg 1984</bibRefCitation>
), i.e. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stach" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[1216,1429,1976,2002]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviempodialis">
<emphasis box="[1216,1429,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">H. breviempodialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martynova" authorityYear="1970" box="[151,316,2012,2038]" class="Collembola" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tianshanica">
